Hi @cmykkid!

1. For this, you can add "filter-onlyAvail" class name ([ref](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-filter.html#classes)) to the Portfolio header cell and only available options will be visible in the select.

```html
<th class="portfolio filter-select filter-onlyAvail" data-priority="critical" data-placeholder="Select a portfolio">Portfolio</th>
```

2. When using the [columnSelector widget](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html), you can add a change event listener on the external select and set it to toggle the desired columns using the [`refreshColumnSelector` method](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html#methods). The above HTML also includes a `data-priority="critical"` attribute to prevent the first column from being hidden.

[Here is a demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/50v3ppwk/8/)

```js
$(function () {

    var $table = $('#task');

    $('select.search').change(function () {
        var $this = $(this),
            val = $this.val();
        // column 0 is set with `data-priority="critical"` so it 
        // is always visible
        if (val === 'In Process') {
            // set visible columns (hide Budget; zero-based index)
            $table.trigger('refreshColumnSelector', [ [1, 2, 4] ]);
        } else if (val === 'Completed') {
            // set visible columns (hide Schedule)
            $table.trigger('refreshColumnSelector', [ [1, 2, 3] ]);
        } else {
            // show all columns
            $table.trigger('refreshColumnSelector', [ [1, 2, 3, 4] ]);
        }
    });

    $table.tablesorter({
        widgets: ["zebra", "filter", "columnSelector"],
        widgetOptions: {
            filter_columnFilters: true,
            filter_external: '.search',
            filter_defaultAttrib: 'data-value',
            // turn off "auto" mode - hide columns based on browser width
            columnSelector_mediaquery: false
        },
        initialized: function () {
            $('select.search').change();
        }
    });
});
```

I didn't include a column selector button to allow the user to toggle visible columns, but you can copy the CSS &amp; HTML from the [main demo](http://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html) if you want one; also, make sure to set the [`columnSelector_container` option](file:///D:/Repos/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-column-selector.html#column-selector-container).

